cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel feedback reduction technique for FDD-based cell-free systems, which involves compressing the channel state information (CSI) feedback. This is a key area of research in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a cell-free system where a group of base stations cooperatively serves users, which is a networking and internet architecture problem.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a technique to maximize the cooperation gain in cell-free systems, which involves controlling the feedback of channel state information.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses downlink pilot precoding, which is a technique used in multimedia communication systems to improve the quality of the received signal.
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - Although less likely, the paper may also fall under this category as it involves processing and compressing channel state information, which could be seen as a language processing task.
